title: AE Specification
text: AE specification analysis provide tables summarize details adverse events. development AE specification analysis contain exported functions prepare_ae_specific: prepare analysis raw datasets format_ae_specific: prepare analysis (mock) outdata proper format tlf_ae_specific: transfer (mock) output dataset RTF table also prepare (optional) additional function extend analysis. extend_ae_specific_inference: add risk difference inference results based M&N method. extend_ae_specific_duration: add average duration AE. extend_ae_specific_events: add average number AE events.

title: Unstratified and Stratified Miettinen and Nurminen Test
text: Binary outcome commonly used endpoint clinical trials. page illustrate conduct unstratified stratified analysis Miettinen Nurminen method (M&N) descrived (Miettinen Nurminen 1985) risk difference analysis R. following statistics can calculated within function rate_compare: estimated risk difference test statistic confidence interval risk difference p-value risk difference.

title: Unstratified and Stratified Miettinen and Nurminen Test
text: Assume data includes two independent binomial samples binary response variables analyzed/summarized data collected clinical design without stratification. Also approach applicable case data collected using stratified clinical design statistician like ignore stratification pooling data strata assuming two independent binomial samples. Assume \(P_i\) proportion success responses test (\(=1\)) control (\(=0\)) group.

previous_headings: Statistical Methods > Unstratified analysis of M&N method
title: Unstratified and Stratified Miettinen and Nurminen Test
text: confidence interval based M&N method given roots \(PD=P_1-P_0\) equation: \[\chi_\alpha^2 = \frac{(\hat{p}_1-\hat{p}_0-PD)^2}{\tilde{V}}\], \(\hat{p}_1\) \(\hat{p}_0\) observed values \(P_1\) \(P_0\), respectively; \(\chi_\alpha^2\) = upper cut point size \(\alpha\) central chi-square distribution 1 degree freedom (\(\chi_\alpha^2 = 3.84\) \(95\)% confidence interval); \(PD\) = difference two population proportions (\(PD=P_1-P_0\)); \[\tilde{V}=[\frac{\tilde{p}_1(1-\tilde{p}_1)}{n_1}+ \frac{\tilde{p}_0(1-\tilde{p}_0)}{n_0}]\frac{n_1+n_0}{n_1+n_0-1}\]; \(n_1\) \(n_0\) sample sizes test control group, respectively; \(\tilde{p}_1\) = maximum likelihood estimate proportion test computed \(\tilde{p}_0+PD\); \(\tilde{p}_0\) = maximum likelihood estimate proportion control constraint \(\tilde{p}_1-\tilde{p}_0=PD\). stated 2-sided \(100(1-\alpha)\)% CI given roots \(PD=P_1-P_0\). bisection algorithm used function obtain two roots (confidence interval) \(PD\).

previous_headings: Statistical Methods > Unstratified analysis of M&N method
title: Unstratified and Stratified Miettinen and Nurminen Test
text: Z-statistic computed : \[Z_{diff}=\frac{\hat{p}_1-\hat{p}_0+S_0}{\sqrt{\tilde{V}}}\] \(\hat{p}_1\) \(\hat{p}_0\) observed values \(P_1\) \(P_0\) respectively, \(S_0\) pre-specified proportion difference null; \(\tilde{p}_1\) = maximum likelihood estimate proportion test computed \(\tilde{p}_0+S_0\); \(\tilde{p}_0\) = maximum likelihood estimate proportion control constraint \(\tilde{p}_1-\tilde{p}_0=S_0\). non-inferiority one-sided equivalence hypothesis \(S_0>0\), p-value, \(Pr(Z\ge Z_{diff}|H_0)\), computed based \(Z_{diff}\) using standard normal distribution. non-inferiority one-sided equivalence hypothesis \(S_0<0\), p-value, \(Pr(Z\le Z_{diff}|H_0)\), computed based \(Z_{diff}\) using standard normal distribution. two-sided supriority test, p-value \(Pr(\chi_{diff}^2\le \chi_1^2|H_0)\), computed based \(\chi_{diff}^2\) using chi-square distribution 1 degree freedom, \(\chi_{diff}^2=Z_{diff}^2\).

title: Unstratified and Stratified Miettinen and Nurminen Test
text: Assume data includes two treatment groups, test control, collected based stratified design. Within stratum two independent binomial samples binary response variables analyzed/summarized. parameter interest difference population proportions test control groups. analysis summaries need performed adjusting stratifying variables.

previous_headings: Statistical Methods > Stratified analysis of M&N method
title: Unstratified and Stratified Miettinen and Nurminen Test
text: confidence interval based M&N method given roots \(PD=P_1-P_0\) equation: \[\chi_\alpha^2 = \frac{(\hat{p}_1^*-\hat{p}_0^*-PD)^2}{\sum_{=1}^(W_i/\sum_{k=1}^{K}W_k)^2\tilde{V}_i}\], \(\hat{p}_s^* = \sum_{=1}^(W_i/\sum_{k=1}^KW_k)\hat{p}_{si}\) \(s=0,1\); \[\tilde{V}_i=[\frac{\tilde{p}_{1i}(1-\tilde{p}_{1i})}{n_{1i}}+\frac{\tilde{p}_{0i}(1-\tilde{p}_{0i})}{n_{0i}}]\frac{n_{1i}+n_{0i}}{n_{1i}+n_{0i}-1}\]; \(W_i\) weight \(^{th}\) strata; $= K = $ number strata, \(=k=\) strata; \(n_{1i}\) \(n_{0i}\) sample sizes \(^{th}\) strata test control group, respectively; \(\hat{p}_{1i}\) \(\hat{p}_{0i}\) = observed proportion \(^{th}\) strata test control, respectively; \(\tilde{p}_{0i}\) \(\tilde{p}_{1i}\) MLE \(P_{0i}\) \(P_{1i}\), respectively, computed constraint \(\tilde{p}_{1i}=\tilde{p}_{0i}+PD\). Similarly unstratified analysis,2-sided \(100(1-\alpha)\)% CI given roots \(PD=P_1-P_0\), bisection algorithm used function obtain two roots (confidence interval) \(PD\).

previous_headings: Statistical Methods > Stratified analysis of M&N method
title: Unstratified and Stratified Miettinen and Nurminen Test
text: Z-statistic computed : \[Z_{diff}=\frac{\hat{p}_1^*-\hat{p}^*_0+S_0}{\sqrt{\sum_{=1}^(W_i/\sum_{k=1}^{K}W_k)^2\tilde{V}_i}}\] \(S_0\) pre-specified proportion difference null; \(\tilde{p}_{0i}\) \(\tilde{p}_{1i}\) MLE \(P_{0i}\) \(P_{1i}\), respectively, computed constraint \(\tilde{p}_{1i}=\tilde{p}_{0i}+S_0\). p-value can calculated stated .

text: formula symbolic description model fitted, form y ~ x. y numeric vector values 0 1, x group information. strata optional vector weights used analysis. specified, unstratified MN analysis used. specified, stratified MN analysis conducted. data optional data frame, list environment containing variables model. found data, variables taken environment (formula), typically environment rate_compare called. delta numeric value set difference two group null. weight weighting schema used stratified MN method. title: Unstratified and Stratified  Miettinen and Nurminen Test — rate_compare
code: ## To conduct the stratified MN analysis with sample size weights: treatment <- c(rep("pbo", 100), rep("exp", 100)) response <- c(rep(0, 80), rep(1, 20), rep(0, 40), rep(1, 60)) stratum <- c(rep(1:4, 12), 1, 3, 3, 1, rep(1:4, 12), rep(1:4, 25)) rate_compare(   formula = response ~ factor(treatment, levels = c("pbo", "exp")),   strata = stratum,   delta = 0,   weight = "ss",   test = "one.sided",   alpha = 0.05 ) #>         est  z_score            p     lower     upper #> 1 0.3998397 5.712797 5.556727e-09 0.2684383 0.5172779

title: Unstratified and Stratified  Miettinen and Nurminen Test in Aggregate Data level — rate_compare_sum
code: ## To conduct the stratified MN analysis with sample size weights: treatment <- c(rep("pbo", 100), rep("exp", 100)) response <- c(rep(0, 80), rep(1, 20), rep(0, 40), rep(1, 60)) stratum <- c(rep(1:4, 12), 1, 3, 3, 1, rep(1:4, 12), rep(1:4, 25)) n0 <- sapply(split(treatment[treatment == "pbo"], stratum[treatment == "pbo"]), length) n1 <- sapply(split(treatment[treatment == "exp"], stratum[treatment == "exp"]), length) x0 <- sapply(split(response[treatment == "pbo"], stratum[treatment == "pbo"]), sum) x1 <- sapply(split(response[treatment == "exp"], stratum[treatment == "exp"]), sum) strata <- c("a", "b", "c", "d") rate_compare_sum(   n0, n1, x0, x1,   strata,   delta = 0,   weight = "ss",   test = "one.sided",   alpha = 0.05 ) #>         est  z_score            p     lower     upper #> 1 0.3998397 5.712797 5.556727e-09 0.2684383 0.5172779
